{"type":"message","id":"ce2c4e86","parentId":"a68e36e8","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:06:42.602Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Task Execution Analysis:**\n\nBased on the investigation so far, here are the likely causes:\n\n**1. Infrastructure Blockers (Critical)**\n- Neo4j is DOWN - task ledger can't record completions properly\n- Gateway is DOWN - agent communication may be affected\n- Task-watcher daemon may be stalled waiting for Neo4j\n\n**2. Task Queue Status**\n- 5 high-priority infrastructure tasks queued for ogedei\n- 4 dev tasks queued for temujin  \n- 1 analysis task queued for jochi\n- All tasks are `.md` files waiting in `~/.openclaw/agents/{agent}/tasks/`\n\n**3. Execution Pipeline**\n- task-watcher.py polls every 15 seconds\n- It spawns claude-agent subprocess for each task\n- If Neo4j is down, task completions can't be logged\n\n**Most Likely Root Cause:**\nThe task-watcher daemon or agent-task-handler may be:\n- Stalled waiting for Neo4j (blocking execution)\n- Not running (process died)\n- Failing silently due to the fs- prefix task_id format issue\n\n**Immediate Action Needed:**\nogedei needs to:\n1. Start Neo4j\n2. Start Gateway\n3. Verify task-watcher is running\n\nShould I escalate this as a critical incident requiring immediate human intervention?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773122792329}}
